channel.title: [Delta = 317] Compile error after adding npc dialogue [Delta = 317]
channel.description:
hey guys, i recently followed an npc dialogue tutorial [url=http://(http://www.sythe.org/showthread.php?t=466082](http://www.sythe.org/showthread.php?t=466082[/url])
and followed everything it said to do, after i finished, i compiled and came up with 1 error that i don't know how to fix:
here is what comes up in compiler error log when i try to compile:
[code]client.java:16238: orphaned case case 89726: ^ 1 error Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
can some1 plz tell me how to fix this? thanx!

item.title: [Delta = 317] Compile error after adding npc dialogue [Delta = 317]
item.dc:creator: @eyeownyew Eyeownyew
item.description:
@eyeownyew wrote:

This is the problem.

Your code:


     case ####:
         [stuff]
     break;
}
     case 89726:
         [stuff]
     break;

You must move the “case 89726:” and the rest of the code inside the bracket ‘}’.
